AI Code Review Iteration1 Performance: Optimization SeverityLow The endpoint lacks a `[ResponseCache]` attribute unlike the similar endpoint `GetPlatformTelemetryLogsBloomFilter` (line 56). Since this endpoint returns a list of supported resource types that likely doesn't change frequently, adding response caching would improve performance and reduce unnecessary load on the server. Here is the suggested code: ``` /// /// Gets the list of supported resource types for platform telemetry logs bloom filters. /// /// /// Request completed successfully [HttpGet("logsBloomFilterSupportedTypes", Name = "OboBloomFilters_GetPlatformTelemetryLogsBloomFilterSupportedTypes")] [ProducesResponseType(StatusCodes.Status200OK)] [ProducesDefaultResponseType(typeof(ErrorResponse))] [ApiConsumesHeader("x-ms-client-request-id", "1f38442f-2f4b-4d8f-b821-00b473bec23b", Description = "Client-generated ID for tracking request end-to-end.")] [ApiProducesHeader("x-ms-request-id", "7d75a902-0211-47d7-80e3-ec2348450402", Description = "Server-generated ID for tracking request end-to-end.")] [AadS2SAuthorization(AmcsS2SRoles.TrustedService)] [ResponseCache(Duration = 900)] public ActionResult> GetPlatformTelemetryLogsBloomFilterSupportedTypes() { List supportedTypes = this.Provider.GetPlatformLogsBloomFilterSupportedResourceTypes(); return this.Ok(supportedTypes); } ``` This comment refers to line 76 to 91 in the new file.
